{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1110 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_75c7e14a3f72ed13","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1110: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $p>q\\geq 2$ be two coprime integers. We call $n$ representable if it is the sum of integers of the form $p^kq^l$, none of which divide each other.\n\nIf $\\{p,q\\}\\neq \\{2,3\\}$ then what can be said about the density of non-representable numbers? Are there infinitely many coprime non-representable numbers? Current best: Yu and Chen \\cite{YuCh22} proved\\[\\frac{n}{(\\log n)^{\\log_23}}\\ll f(n) \\ll \\frac{n}{\\log n}.\\]Yang and Zhao \\cite{YaZh25} improved the lower bound to $f(n)\\gg n/\\log n$. Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_9bc4fb732e14ff23","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1110.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_75c7e14a3f72ed13","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1110","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_75c7e14a3f72ed13","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_9bc4fb732e14ff23","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_9bc4fb732e14ff23","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1110","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_co